modules.description: Converts OCaml numeric types from string representations, detecting precision loss during conversion using Zarith for accurate intermediate calculations. Works with int32, int64, nativeint, and float values, comparing results against OCaml's built-in parsing functions. Generates detailed warnings for precision issues in code, useful for validating input parsing in financial or scientific applications.

This module offers string parsing and conversion functionalities for numeric types, supporting integer and float representations across bases like decimal, hexadecimal, octal, and binary, along with scientific notation and precision tracking. It utilizes type aliases for numeric categories, base specifications, and formatting conventions to define structured representations of numerical data. Use cases include processing formatted input, normalizing numeric strings, and exact conversions in applications requiring base-specific or precision-sensitive calculations.
